            "keysecondary": [],
            "selectiveLogic": 0,
            "content": "Malachia's body is a mountain of disciplined muscle scarred by cage fighting. When he is aroused, the change is subtle but heavy: his scent deepens to leather and iron, his ears flatten against his skull, and his hands, usually gentle, become possessive. He sweats along his spine and the back of his neck. When overwhelmed, he goes still, so still that he seems to stop breathing. He holds the stillness for five to ten seconds before he moves, as if recalibrating. He suppresses all sound except a low chest rumble that vibrates through his ribcage and into whatever he is touching. When he is overstimulated, his muscles lock. He has to be touched slowly, deliberately, to unlock them.",
